{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857479177,"sessionID":"ses_286a5e625ffehqURHaRnf1ZSCP","part":{"id":"prt_d795a9dfa001e7gMYdYERZhE8m","messageID":"msg_d795a948a0010qdxvGWVkxCo2Y","sessionID":"ses_286a5e625ffehqURHaRnf1ZSCP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 Design: Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-006  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Medium\n9: \n10: The Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management component provides comprehensive lifecycle control for sandboxes in the AgentCube system. It handles graceful shutdown, resource cleanup, idle detection, and orphan management while integrating with the existing WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework (AR-004) and Sandbox Creation Handler (AR-005).\n11: \n12: The implementation uses the generated client-go library for Kubernetes API interactions with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs, and dynamic client for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRD operations.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Architecture\n17: \n18: ### High-Level Design\n19: \n20: ```\n21: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n22: в”Ӯ                       External API Clients                                   в”Ӯ\n23: в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                         в”Ӯ\n24: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  Web UI     в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   C