{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857546845,"sessionID":"ses_286a5e625ffehqURHaRnf1ZSCP","part":{"id":"prt_d795ba93e001Ewh92gmjHFZbtE","messageID":"msg_d795b1ce6001UXeEJnuiV9FqVV","sessionID":"ses_286a5e625ffehqURHaRnf1ZSCP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:13","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md"},"error":"File not found: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857546836,"end":1775857546845}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857546865,"sessionID":"ses_286a5e625ffehqURHaRnf1ZSCP","part":{"id":"prt_d795bb074001MG5ZKJQsZ2Ifra","messageID":"msg_d795b1ce6001UXeEJnuiV9FqVV","sessionID":"ses_286a5e625ffehqURHaRnf1ZSCP","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 вҖ” Sandbox еҲӣе»әеӨ„зҗҶеҷЁ\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-005  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Implement the Sandbox creation handler for the WorkloadManager that processes sandbox creation requests from `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, provisions isolated execution environments for agents, and manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources. The handler integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and the generated client-go library (AR-003).\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n17: \n18: The system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from AgentRuntime workload definitions.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid AgentRuntime\n21: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-runtime` exists in namespace `default` with a valid pod template\n22: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"test-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n23: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n24:   1. Validate the request (Kind=AgentRuntime, name and namespace non-empty)\n25:   2. Retrieve the AgentRuntime from informer cache\n26:   3. Build a Sandbox object with generated name `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n27:   4. Create placeholder in Store with status \"pending\"\n28:   5. Register watcher before creating CR to avoid race conditions\n29:   6. Create the Sandbox CR via dynamic client\n30:   7. Wait up to 2 minutes for Sandbox to reach \"running\" status\n31:   8. Resolve Pod IP and build entryPoints from spec.Ports\n32:   9. Update Store with full SandboxInfo including entryPoints\n33:   10. Return HTTP 200 with `CreateSandboxResponse` containing sessionId and entryPoints\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing pod template\n36: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `invalid-runtime` exists in namespace `default` with `spec.template=nil`\n37: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"invalid-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n38: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message containing \"pod template\"\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Create sandbox for non-existent AgentRuntime\n41: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `missing-runtime` exists in namespace `default`\n42: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"missing-runtime\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n43: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"agent runtime not found\"\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with invalid request body\n46: - **GIVEN** a malformed JSON payload\n47: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with invalid JSON\n48: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"Invalid request body\"\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing required fields\n51: - **GIVEN** a request missing the `name` field\n52: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n53: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"name is required\"\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Create sandbox with missing namespace\n56: - **GIVEN** a request missing the `namespace` field\n57: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/agent-runtime` with body `{\"name\": \"test-runtime\"}`\n58: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"namespace is required\"\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n63: \n64: The system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from CodeInterpreter workload definitions.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid CodeInterpreter\n67: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter` exists in namespace `default` with valid template\n68: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{\"name\": \"test-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n69: - **THEN** the server SHALL:\n70:   1. Validate the request (Kind=CodeInterpreter, name and namespace non-empty)\n71:   2. Retrieve the CodeInterpreter from informer cache\n72:   3. Build a Sandbox or SandboxClaim object based on WarmPoolSize\n73:   4. Apply default ports `[{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}]` if spec.Ports is empty\n74:   5. Inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var if AuthMode=picod and publicKey is available\n75:   6. Follow the same creation and wait flow as AgentRuntime\n76:   7. Return HTTP 200 with `CreateSandboxResponse`\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Create SandboxClaim for warm pool\n79: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `warm-interpreter` exists with `WarmPoolSize > 0`\n80: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n81: - **THEN** the server SHALL create a `SandboxClaim` (not full Sandbox) with Kind=\"SandboxClaim\"\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Create full Sandbox for non-warm pool\n84: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `cold-interpreter` exists with `WarmPoolSize=0` or unset\n85: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n86: - **THEN** the server SHALL create a full `Sandbox` with single container named `code-interpreter`\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Create sandbox for non-existent CodeInterpreter\n89: - **GIVEN** no CodeInterpreter named `missing-interpreter` exists\n90: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/v1/code-interpreter` with body `{\"name\": \"missing-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\"}`\n91: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with message \"code interpreter not found\"\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: Sandbox Object Building\n96: \n97: The system SHALL build proper Sandbox/SandboxClaim objects from workload definitions.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Build Sandbox object with correct metadata\n100: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with name `my-runtime` and a sessionID `sess-123`\n101: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n102: - **THEN** the resulting Sandbox SHALL have:\n103:   - Name: `my-runtime-{8-char-random}`\n104:   - APIVersion: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n105:   - Kind: `Sandbox`\n106:   - Labels:\n107:     - `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`: sessionID\n108:     - `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name`: runtime.Name\n109:     - `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name`: sandboxName\n110:     - `managed-by`: `agentcube-workload-manager`\n111:   - Annotations:\n112:     - `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`: SessionTimeout (default \"15m\")\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: Build Sandbox with lifecycle settings\n115: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration` set to 8 hours\n116: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n117: - **THEN** the Sandbox spec SHALL include `lifecycle.shutdownTime` set to `now + MaxSessionDuration`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Build CodeInterpreter Sandbox with auth mode\n120: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `AuthMode=picod` and a public key available\n121: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n122: - **THEN** the container SHALL have environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` set to the public key\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: Build CodeInterpreter Sandbox without auth\n125: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `AuthMode=none`\n126: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxObject()` is called\n127: - **THEN** the container SHALL NOT have `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: Build SandboxClaim for warm pool\n130: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize=5`\n131: - **WHEN** `buildSandboxClaimObject()` is called\n132: - **THEN** the resulting object SHALL have:\n133:   - APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`\n134:   - Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n135:   - Minimal metadata (no full PodSpec)\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Sandbox Creation and Wait Flow\n140: \n141: The system SHALL orchestrate the creation flow with proper synchronization and timeouts.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Register watcher before CR creation\n144: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox object ready to be created\n145: - **WHEN** `createSandbox()` is invoked\n146: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `WatchSandboxOnce()` to register the watcher BEFORE calling `dynamicClient.Create()`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Store placeholder before CR creation\n149: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox object ready to be created\n150: - **WHEN** `createSandbox()` is invoked\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `StoreSandbox()` with status \"pending\" BEFORE creating the CR\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Successfully wait for sandbox running\n154: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR has been created\n155: - **WHEN** the SandboxReconciler notifies the sandbox is running within 2 minutes\n156: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n157:   1. Receive notification from the watcher channel\n158:   2. Resolve Pod IP using `resolvePodIP()`\n159:   3. Build entryPoints from ports and Pod IP\n160:   4. Update Store with status \"running\" and entryPoints\n161:   5. Return the complete SandboxInfo\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: Timeout waiting for sandbox running\n164: - **GIVEN** a Sandbox CR has been created but does not reach running state\n165: - **WHEN** 2 minutes elapse without receiving running notification\n166: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n167:   1. Cancel the wait context\n168:   2. Delete the CR with a 30-second timeout context\n169:   3. Delete the Store placeholder\n170:   4. Return error \"sandbox creation timed out\"\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Pod IP resolution from annotation\n173: - **GIVEN** a running Sandbox with annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name=my-pod`\n174: - **WHEN** `resolvePodIP()` is called\n175: - **THEN** the system SHALL first check the annotation and use `my-pod` as the pod name to look up\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Pod IP resolution from owner reference\n178: - **GIVEN** a running Sandbox without pod name annotation\n179: - **WHEN** `resolvePodIP()` is called\n180: - **THEN** the system SHALL list pods by label `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name` and select the one with OwnerReference matching the Sandbox\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Pod IP resolution failure\n183: - **GIVEN** no running pod exists for the sandbox\n184: - **WHEN** `resolvePodIP()` is called\n185: - **THEN** the system SHALL return error \"no running pod found for sandbox {name}\"\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Requirement: Rollback and Cleanup\n190: \n191: The system SHALL implement proper rollback on creation failures.\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: Rollback on CR creation failure\n194: - **GIVEN** Store placeholder has been created\n195: - **WHEN** dynamic client Create() fails\n196: - **THEN** the system SHALL delete the Store placeholder using `DeleteSandboxBySessionID()`\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Rollback on timeout\n199: - **GIVEN** CR has been created but sandbox never reaches running\n200: - **WHEN** timeout occurs after 2 minutes\n201: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n202:   1. Delete the CR using dynamic client with 30s timeout\n203:   2. Delete the Store placeholder\n204:   3. Return timeout error\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Rollback on Pod IP resolution failure\n207: - **GIVEN** CR has been created and sandbox is running\n208: - **WHEN** Pod IP resolution fails\n209: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n210:   1. Delete the CR\n211:   2. Delete the Store placeholder\n212:   3. Return resolution error\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Handle Store update failure\n215: - **GIVEN** CR is created and running, Pod IP is resolved\n216: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox()` fails\n217: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n218:   1. Log warning about Store inconsistency\n219:   2. CR will be eventually cleaned up by GC\n220:   3. Return the error\n221: \n222: ---\n223: \n224: ### Requirement: Request Validation\n225: \n226: The system SHALL validate CreateSandboxRequest according to defined rules.\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Validate valid request\n229: - **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with `Kind=\"AgentRuntime\"`, `Name=\"test\"`, `Namespace=\"default\"`\n230: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n231: - **THEN** the method SHALL return nil (no error)\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Validate rejects empty name\n234: - **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with empty `Name` field\n235: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n236: - **THEN** the method SHALL return error with message \"name is required\"\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Validate rejects empty namespace\n239: - **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with empty `Namespace` field\n240: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n241: - **THEN** the method SHALL return error with message \"namespace is required\"\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: Validate rejects invalid kind\n244: - **GIVEN** a CreateSandboxRequest with `Kind=\"InvalidKind\"`\n245: - **WHEN** `Validate()` is called\n246: - **THEN** the method SHALL return error with message \"kind is required\" (or invalid kind)\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ### Requirement: Response Building\n251: \n252: The system SHALL build proper CreateSandboxResponse from SandboxInfo.\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Build response with entryPoints\n255: - **GIVEN** a SandboxInfo with:\n256:   - SessionID: `sess-abc-123`\n257:   - SandboxID: `runtime-xyz-789`\n258:   - SandboxName: `my-runtime-abcdef12`\n259:   - EntryPoints: `[{Path: \"/\", Protocol: \"HTTP\", Endpoint: \"10.244.0.5:8080\"}]`\n260: - **WHEN** building the HTTP response\n261: - **THEN** the response SHALL contain:\n262:   ```json\n263:   {\n264:     \"sessionId\": \"sess-abc-123\",\n265:     \"sandboxId\": \"runtime-xyz-789\",\n266:     \"sandboxName\": \"my-runtime-abcdef12\",\n267:     \"entryPoints\": [\n268:       {\n269:         \"path\": \"/\",\n270:         \"protocol\": \"HTTP\",\n271:         \"endpoint\": \"10.244.0.5:8080\"\n272:       }\n273:     ]\n274:   }\n275:   ```\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ### Requirement: Authentication Integration\n280: \n281: The system SHALL integrate with authentication middleware when enabled.\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: Extract auth context when auth enabled\n284: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and request has valid Authorization header\n285: - **WHEN** the handler processes the request\n286: - **THEN** the context SHALL contain:\n287:   - `contextKeyUserToken`: the bearer token\n288:   - `contextKeyServiceAccount`: the service account name\n289:   - `contextKeyNamespace`: the namespace for per-user client caching\n290: \n291: #### Scenario: Reject request without auth header\n292: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and request has no Authorization header\n293: - **WHEN** authMiddleware processes the request\n294: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with message \"Missing authorization header\"\n295: \n296: #### Scenario: Reject invalid token\n297: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and request has invalid token\n298: - **WHEN** authMiddleware calls TokenReview\n299: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 with TokenReview error message\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Use per-user client when auth enabled\n302: - **GIVEN** `EnableAuth=true` and auth context is present\n303: - **WHEN** creating the Sandbox CR\n304: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()` to get per-user dynamic client\n305: \n306: ---\n307: \n308: ### Requirement: Idempotency\n309: \n310: The system SHALL support idempotent creation requests.\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: Return existing session for duplicate request\n313: - **GIVEN** a sandbox creation request for AgentRuntime `test-runtime` has already succeeded with sessionID `sess-123`\n314: - **WHEN** the same request is made again\n315: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n316:   1. Check Store for existing session by workload name\n317:   2. Return the existing sessionID without creating new sandbox\n318:   3. Return HTTP 200 with original CreateSandboxResponse\n319: \n320: ---\n321: \n322: ### Requirement: Error Handling and HTTP Status Mapping\n323: \n324: The system SHALL map internal errors to appropriate HTTP status codes.\n325: \n326: #### Scenario: Map JSON binding error to 400\n327: - **GIVEN** request body is malformed JSON\n328: - **WHEN** `c.ShouldBindJSON()` fails\n329: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with message \"Invalid request body\"\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: Map validation error to 400\n332: - **GIVEN** request fails validation (missing required field)\n333: - **WHEN** `Validate()` returns error\n334: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with validation error message\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Map not found to 404\n337: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is not found in informer cache\n338: - **WHEN** lookup fails\n339: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with appropriate \"not found\" message\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Map internal errors to 500\n342: - **GIVEN** an unexpected internal error occurs (Store failure, K8s API error)\n343: - **WHEN** error is processed\n344: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 500 with message \"internal server error\" (details logged but not exposed)\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: Map timeout to 500\n347: - **GIVEN** sandbox creation times out after 2 minutes\n348: - **WHEN** timeout occurs\n349: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 500 with message \"internal server error\"\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Context Propagation\n354: \n355: The system SHALL properly propagate context through the creation flow.\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Pass context through creation flow\n358: - **GIVEN** a request context with requestID and auth info\n359: - **WHEN** the creation flow executes (validate вҶ’ build вҶ’ create вҶ’ wait)\n360: - **THEN** the context SHALL be passed to all operations for cancellation and timeout handling\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: Handle context cancellation during wait\n363: - **GIVEN** sandbox is waiting for running status\n364: - **WHEN** the parent context is cancelled (e.g., client disconnects)\n365: - **THEN** the wait SHALL be cancelled and resources cleaned up\n366: \n367: ---\n368: \n369: ### Requirement: Timeout Configuration\n370: \n371: The system SHALL enforce configurable timeouts for sandbox operations.\n372: \n373: #### Scenario: Enforce 2-minute creation timeout\n374: - **GIVEN** default timeout configuration\n375: - **WHEN** creating sandbox with `context.WithTimeout(ctx, 2*time.Minute)`\n376: - **THEN** the operation SHALL timeout after 2 minutes if sandbox doesn't reach running\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: Enforce 30-second deletion timeout on rollback\n379: - **GIVEN** rollback is triggered after creation timeout\n380: - **WHEN** deleting the CR\n381: - **THEN** the deletion SHALL use `context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)`\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## File Index\n386: \n387: | Path | Purpose |\n388: |------|---------|\n389: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | HTTP handlers: `handleAgentRuntimeCreate`, `handleCodeInterpreterCreate` |\n390: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go` | `sandboxCreator` struct and `createSandbox()` orchestration |\n391: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go` | `buildSandboxObject()`, `buildSandboxClaimObject()`, `resolvePodIP()`, `buildEntryPoints()` |\n392: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_controller.go` | `SandboxReconciler`, `WatchSandboxOnce()`, sandbox status tracking |\n393: | `pkg/workloadmanager/informers.go` | GVR definitions, `Informers` struct, informer lifecycle |\n394: | `pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client.go` | `K8sClient`, `ClientCache`, `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient()` |\n395: | `pkg/workloadmanager/auth.go` | `authMiddleware`, context keys, token validation |\n396: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL`, `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout`, label/annotation keys |\n397: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox.go` | Sandbox domain types (if not in pkg/apis) |\n398: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go` | Handler unit tests |\n399: | `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator_test.go` | Sandbox creation flow tests |\n400: | `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder_test.go` | Object building tests |\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ## Dependencies\n405: \n406: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n407: |------------|---------|---------|\n408: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated Kubernetes clientset, informers, listers |\n409: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Dynamic client, REST client |\n410: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery, unstructured |\n411: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | Latest | HTTP framework (inherited from AR-004) |\n412: | `github.com/google/uuid` | Latest | UUID generation for sessionID |\n413: | `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | Latest | Test dependency for mock Redis |\n414: \n415: ---\n416: \n417: ## API Endpoints Summary\n418: \n419: | Method | Path | Description |\n420: |--------|------|-------------|\n421: | POST | `/v1/agent-runtime` | Create sandbox from AgentRuntime definition |\n422: | POST | `/v1/code-interpreter` | Create sandbox from CodeInterpreter definition |\n423: \n424: ---\n425: \n426: ## Data Types\n427: \n428: ### CreateSandboxRequest\n429: ```go\n430: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n431:     Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`      // \"AgentRuntime\" or \"CodeInterpreter\"\n432:     Name      string `json:\"name\"`      // workload name\n433:     Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"` // workload namespace\n434: }\n435: ```\n436: \n437: ### CreateSandboxResponse\n438: ```go\n439: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n440:     SessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n441:     SandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n442:     SandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n443:     EntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n444: }\n445: \n446: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n447:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`     // route path prefix\n448:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"` // \"HTTP\" or \"HTTPS\"\n449:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"` // \"host:port\"\n450: }\n451: ```\n452: \n453: ### SandboxInfo (Store model)\n454: ```go\n455: type SandboxInfo struct {\n456:     Kind             string                `json:\"kind\"`             // \"Sandbox\" or \"SandboxClaim\"\n457:     SandboxID        string                `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n458:     SandboxNamespace string                `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n459:     Name             string                `json:\"name\"`\n460:     SessionID        string                `json:\"sessionId\"`\n461:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint   `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n462:     Status           string                `json:\"status\"`           // \"pending\", \"running\", \"failed\"\n463:     CreatedAt        time.Time             `json:\"createdAt\"`\n464:     ExpiresAt        time.Time             `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n465: }\n466: ```\n467: \n468: ---\n469: \n470: ## Integration with client-go\n471: \n472: | Component | Usage |\n473: |-----------|-------|\n474: | `clientset/versioned.Interface` | Get typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n475: | `informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory` | Informer lifecycle management |\n476: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister` | Read-only AgentRuntime queries |\n477: | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterLister` | Read-only CodeInterpreter queries |\n478: | `fake.Clientset` | Unit test mocks |\n479: \n480: ---\n481: \n482: ## Notes\n483: \n484: - Watcher MUST be registered BEFORE creating the CR to avoid race conditions where Sandbox enters running before watcher is ready\n485: - Store placeholder MUST be created BEFORE CR creation for idempotency and rollback\n486: - Dynamic client is used for Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRDs (external to agentcube)\n487: - Per-user K8s client is used when authentication is enabled\n488: - All timeouts are configurable via constants in `defaults.go`\n489: - EntryPoints are built from `spec.Ports` with format: `{PathPrefix, Protocol, PodIP:Port}`\n\n(End of file - total 489 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 вҖ” Sandbox еҲӣе»әеӨ„зҗҶеҷЁ\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-005  \n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n\nImplement the Sandbox creation handler for the WorkloadManager that processes sandbox creation requests from `POST /v1/agent-runtime` and `POST /v1/code-interpreter`, provisions isolated execution environments for agents, and manages the lifecycle of sandbox resources. The handler integrates with the existing HTTP service framework (AR-004) and the generated client-go library (AR-003).\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime Sandbox Creation Endpoint\n\nThe system SHALL expose an HTTP endpoint to create sandboxes from AgentRuntime workload definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Create sandbox from valid AgentRuntime","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857546840,"end":1775857546862}}}}
